Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C/180°C fan/gas mark 6.

Remove the @filo pastry sheets{1/2} from the fridge and bring it to room temperature.
Remove the pastry from the packet and lay flat on the counter, covered with a damp
#tea towel{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @chicken thigh{260%g}(diced) and season with @salt{}
and @black pepper{}. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through,
~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

While the chicken cooks, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).
Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthways), then quarter lengthways
(no need to peel). Chop widthways into small pieces.

Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a #bowl{} and leave to the side.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Return your (now empty) pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle more @oil{}.

Add the onion and carrot and stir-fry until slightly softened, ~{4-5%minutes},
then stir in the @mushrooms{120%g}(sliced) cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce into the veg pan.

Bring to the boil, then turn down the heat, add the @creme fraiche{150%g} and
simmer gently until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, return the chicken to the pan. Season with @salt{}
and @black pepper{} and transfer to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Halve the filo pastry sheets to make squares.

Scrunch each sheet into a very loose ball and place on top of the filling. Repeat
until the whole pie is covered, making sure not to overcrowd the pastry.

Drizzle the whole thing with @oil{} and then bake on the top shelf of your oven
until the filo is golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

When the pie's ready, share it between your #plates{} and dig in. Enjoy!